# Dirac build spec (condensed)

## One-sentence definition
Dirac is a unified communications workspace (“Cursor for messages”) where users triage, understand, and respond fast with an AI copilot across many platforms (start with **Gmail**, but design multi-platform from day one).

## “Cursor for messages” meaning (implementation bar)
- AI must be embedded in workflow (context-aware, action-first).
- Prioritize **manipulation**: summarize / condense / rewrite / extract tasks / rank urgency.
- Clarify with short structured MCQs (don’t chat endlessly).

## Daily loop (core UX)
- Open Unified Inbox → pick thread(s) → read thread → use AI sidebar actions → send/edit → mark done/snooze/tag.

## Top-level pages (keep minimal)
- **Inbox** (Unified)
- **Compose**
- **Activity** (Sent + Drafts)
- **Settings**

## Inbox (Unified) essentials
- Left: thread list (platform icon, sender, snippet, unread, timestamp).
- Center: thread timeline.
- Right: AI sidebar (toggleable).
- Must support: filters, search, multi-select, tag/done/snooze; platform actions only when available.

## AI sidebar (must-have behaviors)
- Always show **explicit scope** (current thread vs selected threads).
- Prefer short, usable outputs (draft/summary/checklist/ranking).
- Quick actions row: Reply / What it means / Summarize / Next actions / More…
- If missing critical info: one MCQ block, max 3 questions; proceed after answers.

## Unified data model (cross-platform)
- Account, Thread/Conversation, Message, Contact/Participant
- Dirac metadata: tags, status, urgency, snoozeUntil, pinned, assignedTo, etc.
- Don’t force Gmail semantics onto everything; keep Dirac-level actions universal.

## MVP scope (recommended)
- Phase 1: Gmail connect, list threads, read thread, reply, compose new email.
- AI: summarize, draft reply, rewrite/shorten, extract tasks/deadlines, rank urgency.
- Local drafts autosave + Activity/Drafts to reopen.
- UI includes multi-platform scaffolding/indicators even if execution is Gmail-only initially.

## Tech stack defaults (if choosing)
- Next.js (App Router) + React + TypeScript (run as a **Node server**, containerized)
- Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Postgres + Prisma
- Auth: Auth.js (NextAuth) or custom OAuth (Gmail OAuth requires safe server-side token handling)
- Jobs: **BullMQ + Redis** with a separate **worker** service; realtime: SSE/WebSockets as needed
- Deployment: follow `dirac-tech-stack-deployment.mdc` (Railway-first, web + worker + Postgres + Redis)
